definition.value: A tetracyclic triterpenoid isolated from the fruiting bodies of Ganoderma hainanense.
An iminium ion resulting from the protonation of the two imine groups of saxitoxin; major species at pH 7.3.
An iminium ion resulting from the protonation of the imine group of tetrodotoxin; major species at pH 7.3.
A carboxy-2-hydroxymuconate semialdehyde having the carboxy group at the 4-position and the aldehyde functijon at the 6-position.
An intermediate metabolite in the detoxification of the active paracetamol metabolite NAPQI
A 5-nonen-2-one in which the double bond adopts a trans-configuration.
A 5-nonen-2-one in which the double bond adopts a cis-configuration.
A  thio-fatty acid that is reduced form of lipoic acid. A potent antioxidant shown to directly destroy superoxide, hydroperoxy and hydroxyl radicals; also has neuroprotective and anti-tumour effects.
An acyclic carotene that is lycopene having a cis-double bond at position 9.
An acyclic carotene that is lycopene having a cis-double bond at position 15.
The hydrochloride salt of thiobenzyl benzyloxycarbonyl-L-lysinate. It is a substrate for a sensitive colorimetric assay for trypsin-like enzymes.
Definition: A 3-oxo-5alpha-steroid formed from corticosterone by reduction across the C4-C5 double bond.
A 3-oxo-5alpha-steroid formed from aldosterone by reduction across the C4-C5 double bond.

An L-lysine derivative that is L-lysine in which the amino group is replaced by a [(benzyloxy)carbonyl]amino group and the carboxy group is replaced by a (benzylsulfanyl)carbonyl group. It is a substrate for a sensitive colorimetric assay for trypsin-like enzymes.
A primary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of thiobenzyl benzyloxycarbonyl-L-lysinate resulting from the protonation of the primary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

A member of the class of imidazoles that is 1H-imidazole substituted by (4-cyanophenyl)methyl and [4-(3-chlorophenyl)-3-oxopiperazin-1-yl]methyl groups at positions 1 and 5, respectively. It is a dual inhibitor of FPTase and GGPTase-I.

A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising a linear tetrasaccharide chain of alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (2->6), (1->4) and (1->6), to the N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residue at the reducing end of which is also linked (1->3) a further beta-D-galactose residue.
A lactol that is DIBOA in which the hydrogen at position 7 is replaced by a methoxy group. It has been isolated from the maize plants.

A member of the class of ureas that is urea in which three of the four hydrogens are replaced by ethyl and 4-[4,4-bis(4-fluorophenyl)butyl]piperazin-1-yl groups. An atypical antipsychotic which was in clinical development for the treatment of schizophrenia and substance-related disorders. It is a potent 5-HT2A antagonist and used in veterinary medicine because of its sedative effect on pigs.
A 1-ribosyltriazole that is ribavirin in which the hydroxy group at the 5'-position is replaced by a diphosphate group. It is the metabolite of the antiviral agent ribavirin.
A member of the class of triazoles that is 1H-1,2,4-triazole substituted by an aminocarbonyl group at position 3. It is the major catabolite and aglycon of ribavirin.
A  1-ribosyltriazole that is ribavirin in which the carbamoyl group at position 3 is replaced by a carboxy group. It is a catabolite and impurity of ribavirin.
A tertiary ammonium ion that is conjugate acid of amperozide resulting from the protonation of the piperazine moiety; major species at pH 7.3.
The hydrochloride salt of amperozide.
A pyrrolidin-2-one substituted by two ethyl groups at position 3.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprising a linear trisaccharide chain of alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3) and (1->3), to the N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residue at the reducing end of which is also linked (1->6) an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue.
A  tertiary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the two tertiary amino groups of cis-flupenthixol.
The dihydrochloride salt of cis-flupenthixol.
An azacycloalkane that is cyclohexane in which one of the carbons is replaced by a nitrogen. It is a metabolite of cadaverine, a polyamine found in the human intestine.

A cyclodepsipeptide with formula C27H41N3O5. It was originally isolated from the fungus Beauveria sp. FO-6979 during a screening program for inhibitors of lipid droplet accumulation in murine macrophages. It is an inhibitor of acyl-CoA: cholesterol acyltransferase (ACAT) and effective at reducing atherogenic lesions of the artery and heart in mouse models.
A hydrochloride salt obtained by reaction of 1-[1-(1-benzothiophen-2-yl)cyclohexyl]piperidine with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid.
An amino pentasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group.

A branched amino octasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 6 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man group.
A 1,2,5-oxadiazole substituted by an oxido, cyano and phenyl groups at positions 2, 3 and 4, respectively. It is a vasodilator and inhibitor of platelet aggregation.
